OL,6,FBut Louise Oakley, for the Solicitor
OL,7,FGeneral, said the sentencing judge had
OL,8,Fgiven too much weight to mitigating
OL,9,Ffeatures in the case, including that
OL,10,FMahmood had shown remorse, suffered
OL,11,Ffrom post-traumatic stress disorder
OL,12,Fand flashbacks, and had suffered other
OL,13,Ffamily bereavements.
OL,15,FShe said said they "did not serve to
OL,16,Freduce the offender's culpability or
OL,17,Fthe seriousness of the offence".
